This paper deals with social networks and link analysis, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Social and Behavioral Sciences (cs.SOC). The paper also mentions the use of time granularity, which is a common topic in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques, which falls under the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL).
